<h2> Exploritory Experiments</h2>

<h5>Contextual Inquiry</h5>
<p>A method of user research where a researcher observes users behaving in their normal context</p>

<h5>A Day in the Life</h5>
  <p>A qualitative research method that uses customer ethnography to deepen understanding of a customer's jobs, pains and gains </p>

  <h5>Concierge Experiment</h5>
  <p> Perform the services you are offereing as a concierge at a hotel might learn from your customers</p>

  <h5> Customer Interviews </h5>
  <h5> Discovery Survey</h5>
  <h5>Web Analytics </h5>



<h2> Testing Value Proposition Experiments</h2>



  <h5>Wizard of Oz MVP</h5>
  <p> Giving the user a nice front end experience, while hiding from them all the operations in the back</p>



  <h5>Pop up shop</h5>
  <p>A temporary short term store front. Used to test a company's store viability, generate brand awareness and interact with customers </p>

  <h5>Confrence Room Pilot</h5>
  <p>Running a real time, step by step demonstration of a process with all its compartments</p>

  <h5>Prototype</h5>
  <p>An early model/design of your product</p>

  <h5>Fake Front Door</h5>
  <p>Estabilishment of a facade that has nothing functional behind the scenes. It is used to test an idea without investing in backend development</p>

  <h5>Judo Test</h5>
  <p>Copying your competitor's product and rebranding it as your own</p>


